description: President Biden urged restraint in Israel's response to the attack by Iran when he spoke with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. Meanwhile, protests broke out around the United States to try to stop the bloodshed in Gaza. NBC News' Gabe Gutierrez reports
title: White House tries to prevent a wider war in the Mideast

description: Two days after Iran launched hundreds of missiles, drones and cruise missiles at Israel, Israel said it would strike back. A senior Israeli official said a military response is necessary but should not provoke a regional war. NBC News' Richard Engel reports.
title: Israel's military vows military response after Iran attack

description: Chatham House Associate Fellow Bilal Saab tells Yamiche Alcindor the Iranian strikes on Israel signify that Iran has the ability to potentially mount a more significant attack should they desire to in the future. Saab joined retired Adm. James Stavridis on Meet the Press NOW.
title: Iranian strikes were meant as a ‘cease and desist message’ to Israel, says Middle East expert

description: A bishop was stabbed during a livestreamed service at Christ the Good Shepherd Church in Sydney, Australia, the city’s second stabbing incident in two days. Hundreds of people rushed to the scene in anger and some clashed with riot police.
title: Bishop stabbed during livestreamed Sydney church service

description: Iran's attack on Israel left the United States and its allies scrambling to avoid a wider conflict as the world waits to see what comes next.
title: The shadowy war between Israel and Iran has exploded into view. What's next?

description: An investigation of five fur farms in China found a high risk of diseases developing that could jump from animals to humans, said  Humane Society International.
title: High risk of animal-to-human diseases developing in some China fur farms, welfare group says

description: Organizers of the Beijing Half Marathon said they were investigating after video appeared to show three African runners allowing a Chinese athlete to win.
title: Beijing half marathon organizers investigate Chinese runner's controversial win

description: Georgian lawmakers came to blows in Tbilisi as ruling party legislators looked set to advance a controversial bill on "foreign agents" that has been criticized by Western countries and sparked protests at home.
title: Watch lawmakers brawl as Georgian Parliament considers 'foreign agent' bill

description: Five years after a devastating fire left the spire and roof badly damaged, restorative repairs of Notre Dame Cathedral in Paris are nearing completion. NBC’s Keir Simmons reports for TODAY.
title: Notre Dame Cathedral to reopen 5 years after massive fire

description: The Australian city of Sydney was hit by another stabbing incident on Monday, two days after a man stabbed six people to death in a busy shopping mall before being shot by a police officer.
title: Multiple people injured in new stabbing incident in Sydney, Australia

description: The U.S. is urging restraint after Israel was bombarded by hundreds of missiles and drones from Iran over the weekend in retaliation for its attack on the Iranian consulate in Damascus. NBC’s Richard Engel reports for TODAY and White House national security council spokesperson John Kirby weighs in on how to avoid a wider conflict in the region.
title: Israel weighs response after Iran’s missile and drone barrage

description: The man who fatally stabbed six people at a mall in Sydney had a long history of mental illness and frustrations with women, his father told Australian media. Andrew Cauchi said he was devastated by news that his son, Joel, had killed people at a mall in Sydney’s beachside suburb of Bondi and apologized for his son's actions.
title: Sydney stabbing assailant's parents say he was a 'very sick boy'

description: Australian police are examining why a lone assailant who stabbed six people to death in a Sydney shopping mall targeted women while avoiding men.
title: Australian police investigate why women were targeted in Sydney stabbing attack

description: A former government adviser raped a colleague in a Parliament House office, an Australian judge found, dismissing a defamation suit in a case that has gripped the nation.
title: Australian judge finds staffer raped colleague in Parliament office

description: President Joe Biden thanked the U.S. fighter squadrons that helped defend Israel from a drone and missile attack by Iran. In a video posted to social media on Sunday, Biden said, "You make me proud."
title: 'You're incredible:' Biden thanks U.S. fighter squadrons that helped defend Israel
